The paper focuses on the design of an incentive mechanism for mobile crowd sensing (MCS) systems with multiple data requesters. This involves the use of game theory and mechanism design, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of the incentive mechanism with the data aggregation mechanism, which falls under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the importance of computational efficiency, which is a key concern in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the aggregated results, which is a concern in the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
